HEADWORD: Keta
<hw>Ke"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Perh. of Amer. Indian
origin.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small salmon (<spn>Oncorhynchus
keta</spn>) of inferior value, which in the autumn runs up all the
larger rivers between San Francisco and Kamchatka.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

